25|$|Traditionally, the {{obligations}} of the husband include providing for his wife. He is obligated to provide for her sustenance for her benefit; in exchange, he is also entitled to her income. However, this is a right <b>to</b> <b>the</b> <b>wife,</b> and she can release her husband of the obligation of sustaining her, and she can then keep her income exclusively for herself. The document that provides {{for this is the}} ketuba.|$|E
