25|$|Late nineteenth century: Ahhotep I {{was thought}} <b>to</b> be <b>the</b> <b>wife</b> of Seqenenre Tao. The coffins of Deir el-Bahari and Dra' Abu el-Naga' were both {{thought to be}} hers by some experts. Ahhotep II was thought <b>to</b> be <b>the</b> <b>wife</b> of Amenhotep I. Some thought the coffin from the Deir el-Bahari cache belonged <b>to</b> <b>the</b> queen called Ahhotep II in this scheme.|$|R
